In addition, it is not common for fattening families to play sports, which is true for most families of today's schoolchildren - only 15 percent of children answered that their parents will find time for active movement at least once a week.
A survey of 900 children.
The survey was conducted at the end of last year’s school year and was attended by almost 900 children from elementary schools from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second year of the event Obesity is not a coincidence, which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 pupils from grades 4 to 8 have participated in the project.
Proper diet and sufficient exercise in the family is one of the determining factors that causes a dramatic increase in the number of overweight or even obese children.
“Only half of the respondents, for example, reported having breakfast-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-sniff-s five times a day, which is one of the basic assumptions of proper nutrition.”
No breakfast and no evening sausage
Experts point out that for healthy development, relative details are also essential, including, for example, the regular time of family breakfasts.
In the Czech Republic, only 23 percent of schoolchildren have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
And the worst part was finding out that in a dozen households, they don’t eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in families of obese children, unhealthy fries are consumed much more often.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonade every day (70 percent).
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed regularly play sports, their parents had less than half a result - 15 percent.
Set up your own diet
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to compile their own diet according to their own taste and opinion.
"The nutritional preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 years are far from ideal in terms of healthy nutrition."
Among their favorite foods are a lot of floury, meaty and sweet dishes.
"The great popularity of sweet lemonades is particularly alarming," the study's final report said.
For lunch as the main meal, pasta triumphed just above the poultry.
But the children practically did not want legumes at all and the popularity of fish and lunch vegetable dishes is also low.
Predisposition to health
At the same time, the survey showed that children are willing to adjust their eating habits if they get the right information.
"In the control group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the end of the Obesity education lecture, there was a significant shift in preferences towards the principles of healthy nutrition in a number of cases," the results of the project said.
It was striking, for example, for sweet lemonades, where more children would start to give preference to plain water.
Children were also much more likely to check poultry and fish as the main food of the day and limit sweet foods and dumplings.
