7 Lessons from a Lost Interview with Steve Jobs in a Movie Heading to the Movies This Week
After Steve Jobs died on October 5, the opinions of people began to emerge who compared him to Henry Ford - and chose him for his genius as the Greatest Modern Inventor.
At the recently rediscovered interview with Jobs, which was aired for a special movie that is heading to the cinemas this week, it will be for all Apple fans the fact that his creative mind has perfectly understood the business processes and workflows behind his products.
