In 1995, Bob Cringely worked on the TV show Triumph of Computer Fools, which dealt with the dawn of personal computers. During the filming, a unique, more than hourly interview took place.
It had been ten years since Jobs had been forced to leave Apple, and had been busy working with his new computer company NeXT, and eagerly watched as the general public embraced the internet.
