The technological genius that has led the company to its unshakable position is now replaced by people who have no idea of good or bad products - skill and technical knowledge are essential.
This is exactly what happened at Xerox.
Xerox could have owned literally the entire computer industry.
It could have been ten times bigger than it was, it could have been Microsoft in the 1990s...
Instead of winning, they won a loss.
How to take innovation as an art form:
“Between an excellent idea and an excellent product is a long journey and a lot of work... and as that great idea evolves, it changes and grows.”
During that time, you will learn a lot about him.
You have to make a number of compromises - certain things just electrons, glass, robots or factories do not make.
